title: Left of Black | Jazz Saxophonist Joshua Redman
description: Jazz legend Joshua Redman joined Duke Professor Mark Anthony Neal at one of Durham's iconic pubs, The Pinhook, for a stirring discussion about the state of jazz, his own musical journey, and the legacy of his father–– great jazz saxophonist Walter Dewey Redman. Duke Performances brought Redman to Durham to stage his ongoing tribute concert, "Still Dreaming," dedicated to the life, music, and memory of his father and his band: Old and New Dreams. This conversation was recorded for Left of Black on February 14, 2020 and was co-sponsored by the Duke Department of African and African American Studies, the Forum for Scholars and Publics at Duke University, The Pinhook, and Pie Pushers.
